						               													<description>Party-game where players have to answer questions, mime or draw objects with a &amp;quot;limp&amp;quot; pen...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this party game, players move one of two hippo pawns over an 8-shaped track.The fields they land on determine the task they have to fulfill (for this, they also draw a card) - in most cases, the other players try to guess the word/phrase that was intended: &amp;#10;- Draw an item with a wobbly pen&amp;#10;- Take a sip of water and gargle the word&amp;#10;- Group acting (together with one or more players they chose)&amp;#10;Other tasks include&amp;#10;- Reading out a text - now everyone in turn has to say a word connecting to the text within three seconds. Players who fail to do that are out of this task round; the last player &amp;quot;standing&amp;quot; receiving points. &amp;#10;- Rolling a &amp;quot;poker&amp;quot; die. A saxophone means a five point chip and the chance to roll again. When a lemon is rolled, all chips of this round are lost. The player can stop rolling any time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each kind of field has its own scoring rules. The first player to score 100 points is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
